Dear Professor Kim, &#8239; &#8239;

Thank you for submitting your manuscript to Computer Networks. &#8239;

I have completed my evaluation of your manuscript. The reviewers recommend reconsideration of your manuscript following minor revision and modification. I invite you to resubmit your manuscript after addressing the comments below. Please resubmit your revised manuscript by Apr 27, 2021.

When revising your manuscript, please consider all issues mentioned in the reviewers&#39; comments carefully: please outline every change made in response to their comments and provide suitable rebuttals for any comments not addressed. Please note that your revised submission may need to be re-reviewed. &#8239; &#8239;

To submit your revised manuscript, please log in as an author at https://www.editorialmanager.com/comnet/, and navigate to the &#34;Submissions Needing Revision&#34; folder under the Author Main Menu. &#8239; &#8239;

Computer Networks values your contribution and I look forward to receiving your revised manuscript.&#65532; &#8239;

Kind regards,&#8239; &#8239;

Tommaso Melodia &#8239;

Editor-in-Chief &#8239;

Computer Networks &#8239;

Editor and Reviewer comments: &#8239; &#8239;

Reviewer #1: Thank you for carefully incorporating prior comments. In the current version, a few additional recommendations:
- Given you are operating at high SNR, please be explicit when making comparisons to prior work. Most prior works use SNRs in the range of ~10-15 dB, whereas 30 dB is not a fair comparison. The range of SNR is also relevant since generalization of learned behaviors is sensitive to those changes. This context is relevant to both the abstract, the conclusions (now incorporated), and the primary text. E.g., are you setting the proper expectations in the abstract when you give performance figures? are you fairly comparing performance in Table 8?
- The confusion matrices in Fig 5 and 10 still have numbers that are far too small to read. Recommend eliminating scientific notation and increasing font size within confusion matrices ~3x. You can make better use of the white space to avoid expanding the actual image size.
- Paper still needs a thorough proof-reading for English language usage. E.g., &#34;Despite attracting wider attention in diverse utilization, UAVs has illegal&#39;s abused in privacy disclosure, ...&#34;

Reviewer #2: All my comments are satisfied, I think this paper is suitable for publication.
&#8239; &#8239;

