Editor and Reviewer comments: &#8239; &#8239;



Reviewer #1: In my opinion, based on authors corrections this manuscript can be accepted for publication.


Reviewer #2: The paper titled &#34;RBF-SVM Kernel-based Model for Detecting DDoS Attacks in SDN-based VANET&#34; has been found interesting which discussed the identification of DDoS attacks in order to reach the optimal selection towards increasing the rate of detection, but has some major drawbacks:
1. The contributions are poorly written, this needs to be expanded more for the better understanding of the proposed work.
2. Show the comparative analysis with other QoS metrics and display the percentage of proposed framework over the existing models. Use line graphs to display the results.
3. Explain with the help of flowchart the identification of DDoS attacks in Vanet&#39;s or propose the algorithm how the attack has been identified.
4. The terminologies used in Figure 1 should be thoroughly explained for the better understanding.
5. The whole manuscript needs the careful proofreading as there are lot many spelling mistakes and sentences doesn&#39;t have any uniformity.
&#8239; &#8239;



